            <commentid>260</commentid>
            <who name="Elie Dumas">eliedumas</who>
            <bug_when>2006-08-02 15:07:00 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>In a layout whose overflow property was set to &#39;hidden&#39;, a QxWindow whose overflow property was set to &#39;scroll&#39; (or &#39;srollX&#39;, &#39;scrollY&#39;)appears strangely when it overflows the layout. 
The QxWindow image refreshes not well, it lets some traces on screen. If you refresh the display (e.g. simply by resizing the web browser), then the QxWindow appears all right (the overflowing part is hidden).</thetext>
